# Dashboard Real-Time Data Integration

## Goal

The `/Dashboard` page currently displays hardcoded dummy data across its three
display components ([SectionCards](file:///c:/Users/santo/OneDrive/Desktop/sunny/GodsEye%20-%20FrontEnd%20with%20Backend%20py/GodsEye%20-%20FrontEnd/godseye/components/section-cards.tsx#15-88), [ChartAreaInteractive](file:///c:/Users/santo/OneDrive/Desktop/sunny/GodsEye%20-%20FrontEnd%20with%20Backend%20py/GodsEye%20-%20FrontEnd/godseye/components/chart-area-interactive.tsx#676-856), [DataTable](file:///c:/Users/santo/OneDrive/Desktop/sunny/GodsEye%20-%20FrontEnd%20with%20Backend%20py/GodsEye%20-%20FrontEnd/godseye/components/data-table.tsx#40-222)).

The `/optimize` page already fetches and persists all the real data to
`useProductStore` (Zustand + `localStorage`):
- SOV snapshots and query-level insights via `/api/sov`
- `optimizationAnalysis` (Perplexity), `googleOverviewAnalysis` (Google AI Mode)
- Lists of all products, queries used per engine

The plan is to **share this already-persisted data** with the Dashboard by
reading from `useProductStore` (and triggering a fresh `/api/sov` fetch if the
data isn't loaded yet). No logic is duplicated.

---

## Data Mapping

| Dashboard Widget | Source in Store / API |
|---|---|
| **Brand Coverage** card | `SOVSnapshot.global_sov_score` for client brand |
| **Mentions** card | `SOVSnapshot.total_queries_analyzed` (number of queries where brand appeared) |
| **Visibility Rate** card | `SOVSnapshot.citation_score` |
| **Brand Coverage chart** | One data point per `analyzed_at` date in historical snapshots per engine with brand name |
| **Brand Ranking table** | Computed from competitors found in `optimizationAnalysis.competitive_landscape_analysis` |
| **Top Prompts table** | `sov_query_insights`: prompt, visibility, dominance rate, text snippet |
| **Citations Rank table** | `processedSources` / `sourceLinks` from the product store |
| **Your Brands Citations table** | Filtered `sourceLinks` where brand is referenced |

---

## Proposed Changes

### New Shared Hook

#### [NEW] `hooks/use-dashboard-data.ts`

A single React hook that:
1. Reads `currentProductId`, `optimizationAnalysis`, `googleOverviewAnalysis`, `processedSources`, `sourceLinks` from `useProductStore`.
2. If `currentProductId` exists, calls `/api/sov?productId=...&engine=<activeEngine>` to fetch `latestSnapshot`, `previousSnapshot`, and `insights`.
3. Returns a typed `DashboardData` object consumed by all three Dashboard components.
4. Returns `isLoading: true` and `hasNoData: true` states for empty-state handling.

---

### Component Updates

#### [MODIFY] [components/section-cards.tsx](file:///c:/Users/santo/OneDrive/Desktop/sunny/GodsEye%20-%20FrontEnd%20with%20Backend%20py/GodsEye%20-%20FrontEnd/godseye/components/section-cards.tsx)

- Accept a `data: DashboardData | null` prop.
- Show live values for Brand Coverage, Mentions, Visibility Rate from `latestSnapshot`.
- Show delta badge by comparing `latestSnapshot` vs `previousSnapshot`.
- Show a skeleton/empty-state card when `hasNoData` is true.

#### [MODIFY] [components/chart-area-interactive.tsx](file:///c:/Users/santo/OneDrive/Desktop/sunny/GodsEye%20-%20FrontEnd%20with%20Backend%20py/GodsEye%20-%20FrontEnd/godseye/components/chart-area-interactive.tsx)

- Accept a `chartData: ChartPoint[]` prop instead of using hardcoded `chartData`.
- `ChartPoint` = `{ date, client, compA, compB, compC }` (same shape, already used).
- When `hasNoData`, render a placeholder empty chart with a "No data yet" overlay.

#### [MODIFY] [components/data-table.tsx](file:///c:/Users/santo/OneDrive/Desktop/sunny/GodsEye%20-%20FrontEnd%20with%20Backend%20py/GodsEye%20-%20FrontEnd/godseye/components/data-table.tsx)

- Accept a `data: DashboardData | null` prop.
- Derive `brandRanking`, `topPrompts`, `citationsRank`, `brandCitations` from the live `DashboardData` object.
- Fall back to an empty-state row ("No data – run an analysis in Optimize first") when `hasNoData`.

#### [MODIFY] [app/Dashboard/page.tsx](file:///c:/Users/santo/OneDrive/Desktop/sunny/GodsEye%20-%20FrontEnd%20with%20Backend%20py/GodsEye%20-%20FrontEnd/godseye/app/Dashboard/page.tsx)

- Call `useDashboardData(activeEngine)` hook.
- Pass the returned data down to [SectionCards](file:///c:/Users/santo/OneDrive/Desktop/sunny/GodsEye%20-%20FrontEnd%20with%20Backend%20py/GodsEye%20-%20FrontEnd/godseye/components/section-cards.tsx#15-88), [ChartAreaInteractive](file:///c:/Users/santo/OneDrive/Desktop/sunny/GodsEye%20-%20FrontEnd%20with%20Backend%20py/GodsEye%20-%20FrontEnd/godseye/components/chart-area-interactive.tsx#676-856), [DataTable](file:///c:/Users/santo/OneDrive/Desktop/sunny/GodsEye%20-%20FrontEnd%20with%20Backend%20py/GodsEye%20-%20FrontEnd/godseye/components/data-table.tsx#40-222).
- Remove the import of the static [data.json](file:///c:/Users/santo/OneDrive/Desktop/sunny/GodsEye%20-%20FrontEnd%20with%20Backend%20py/GodsEye%20-%20FrontEnd/godseye/app/Dashboard/data.json).

